11/05/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The Croatian Interior Ministry is offering a reward of about $50,000 for any information that could lead to locating and detaining Gen Ante Gotovina, a fugitive wanted by the UN war crimes tribunal.
The ministry announced the reward Saturday (10 May).
The announcement was greeted with strong criticism by the opposition nationalist Croatian Democratic Union.
(HINA, PBS BiH - 10/05/03)
